  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies color primaries using ITU-T H.273 (CICP) numeric codes.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspacePrimariesCicp` specifies a set of color primaries using the numeric
codes defined in ITU-T H.273 (also known as ISO 23091-2 / CICP). These values
identify the chromaticity coordinates of the red, green, blue, and white points
that define a color space's gamut.

Pass a value from this enumeration to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp*>
along with a transfer function to create a fully described color space.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create an sRGB-compatible color space using Rec. 709 primaries
// and the IEC 61966-2-1 (sRGB) transfer function
using var colorSpace = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec709,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Iec6196621);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
